**Solution**
Given $z = 2\sqrt{3} + 2i$

**Modulus:**
$$
|z| = \sqrt{(2\sqrt{3})^2 + 2^2}
= \sqrt{12 + 4}
= \sqrt{16}
= 4
$$

**Argument:**
$$
\tan \theta = \frac{\text{Imaginary part}}{\text{Real part}}
= \frac{2}{2\sqrt{3}} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}
$$
Hence,
$$
\theta = 30^\circ \text{ or } \frac{\pi}{6} \text{ radians.}
$$

So the modulus is $4$ and the argument is $\frac{\pi}{6}$.

